Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 20 February 2024
Welcome to AugmentedWorks! We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users’ data. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our suite of Augmented Reality (AR) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) applications (“Apps”). By accessing and using our Apps, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect personal and non-personal information that you provide to us directly or automatically through your use of our Apps. This includes:
Personal Information
: Your name, email address, and other contact information when you create an account, participate in our forums, or contact us directly.
Device and Usage Information
: Data about your device and how you use our Apps, including your device type, operating system, IP address, app usage data, and location information.
Content Created
: Information and content you create using our Apps, including AR objects placed in the real world and any AI-generated content.
Location Data
: Precise geolocation data to provide location-based services and content within our Apps.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide, maintain, and improve our Apps and services.
Personalize your experience and tailor content based on your preferences and interactions.
Communicate with you about updates, support, and administrative messages.
Enhance app security, monitor analytics, and conduct research to develop new technologies and services.
Comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms and conditions.
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information with:
Service providers who perform services on our behalf.
Law enforcement, government officials, or other third parties if required by law or to protect the rights and safety of our users and the public.
Affiliated companies within our corporate group for operational purposes.
A buyer or other successor in the event of a merger, divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some or all of AugmentedWorks’ assets.
4. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information. However, no internet-based service can guarantee complete security.
5. Children’s Privacy
Our Apps are not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without obtaining parental consent.
6. Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict the use of your personal information.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the “Effective Date” at the top.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at info@augmentedworks.com.